The paper discusses theoretical advances and algorithmic developments in sparsity-aware learning and compressed sensing, which are topics that are typically covered in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and systems and control (cs.SI). Given that the paper focuses on both batch processing and online processing techniques, it is likely to be relevant to a broad range of sub-fields within computer science. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.IT, followed by cs.SP, cs.NA, and cs.SI.
